Subject: [PATCH 1/3] video: fbdev: fsl-dcu: fix compiling warning for ret assignment

drivers/video/fbdev/fsl-dcu-fb.c:874:2: warning: suggest parentheses around assignment used as truth value [-Wparentheses]
  if (ret = (fb_alloc_cmap(&info->cmap, 16, 0)))
  ^
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/video/fbdev/fsl-dcu-fb.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/fbdev/fsl-dcu-fb.c b/drivers/video/fbdev/fsl-dcu-fb.c
index 89f7917..32ad18b 100644
--- a/drivers/video/fbdev/fsl-dcu-fb.c
+++ b/drivers/video/fbdev/fsl-dcu-fb.c
@@ -870,7 +870,8 @@ static int install_framebuffer(struct fb_info *info)
 	info->flags = FBINFO_FLAG_DEFAULT;
 	info->pseudo_palette = &mfbi->pseudo_palette;
 
-	if (ret = fb_alloc_cmap(&info->cmap, 16, 0))
+	ret = fb_alloc_cmap(&info->cmap, 16, 0);
+	if (ret)
 		return ret;
 
 	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&info->modelist);
